PREHEAT oven to 375 degrees F. COMBINE pasta, oil and 2 lightly beaten eggs in large bowl; press onto bottom and up side of 10-inch pie plate. BAKE for 7 to 10 minutes or until set. COMBINE creamed spinach, remaining eggs, ricotta cheese, 1/2 cup mozzarella cheese, half-and-half, onion, Parmesan, parsley and basil; spoon into pasta shell. Top with remaining mozzarella. BAKE for 30 to 35 minutes or until knife inserted near center comes out clean; cool for 10 minutes before serving.